e Qing Formation in World-Historical Time, Harvard University Asia Center, 2004.(族群、認同與國家/新清史) 60. Susan Huang, Shih-shan. Picturing the True Form: Daoist Visual Culture in Traditional China, Harvard University Asia Center, 2012.(視覺與圖像/道教) 61. Swope, Kenneth M. The Military Collapse of China's Ming Dynasty, 1618-44, Routledge, 2013.(族群、認同與國家) 62. Szonyi, Michael. Practicing Kinship: Lineage and Descent in Late Imperial China, Stanford University Press, 2002. 63. Teng, Emma Jinhua. Taiwan's Imagined Geography: Chinese Colonial Travel Writing and Pictures, 1683-1895, Harvard University Asia Center, 2006.(旅遊與書寫/地理想像/臺灣) 64. Theiss, Janet M. Disgraceful Matters: The Politics of Chastity in Eighteenth-Century China, University of California Press, 2005.(性別與社會/貞節政治) 65. Tian, Xiaofei .Visionary Journeys: Travel Writings from Early Medieval and Nineteenth-Century China, Harvard University Asia Center, 2012.(旅遊與書寫) 66. Vitiello, Giovanni. The Libertine's Friend: Homosexuality and Masculinity in Late Imperial China, University of Chicago Press, 2011.(性別與社會/同性戀/陽剛) 67. Wang, Richard G. The Ming Prince and Daoism: Institutional Patronage of an Elite, Oxford University Press, USA, 2012.(信仰、宗教與社會/道教/贊助/仕紳) 68. Wang, Yanning. Beyond the boudoir: Women's poetry on travel in late imperial China, ProQuest, UMI Dissertation Publishing, 2011.(旅遊與書寫/女性/詩) 69. Wilcox, Lorraine. Raising the Dead and Returning Life: Emergency Medicine of the Qing Dynasty, The Chinese Medicine Database, 2012.(醫療與社會/外科/清代) 70. Wills Jr, John E. China and Maritime Europe, 1500-1800: Trade, Settlement, Diplomacy, and Missions, Cambridge University Press, 2010.(文化交流/歐洲) 71. Woo, X. L. Empress Dowager Cixi: China's Last Dynasty and the Long Reign of a Formidable Concubine : Legends and Lives During the Declining Days of the Qing Dynasty, Algora Publishing, 2003)(政治文化/慈禧/生活/傳說) 72. Wu, Cuncun. Homoerotic Sensibilities in Late Imperial China, Routledge, 2004.(性別與醫療/同性戀) 73. Zarrow, Peter. After Empire: The Conceptual Transformation of the Chinese State, 1885-1924, Stanford University Press, 2012.(族群、認同與國家) 74. Zhang, Cong Ellen. Transformative Journeys: Travel and Culture in Song China, Univ of Hawaii Pr, 2010.(旅遊與書寫) 75. Zhou, Xiaoyan. Qing Perceptions of Anti-Chinese Violence in the United States: Case Studies from the American West, VDM Verlag1, 2009.(族群、認同與國家/移民/反華) 










        
             
            

